PROGRAM FILE 77: ERROR - REFERENCE TO ARRAY AND SIMPLE 
        VARIABLE OF SAME NAME.
    ANSI STANDARD 6.4

SECTION 77.1: ERROR - REFERENCE TO ARRAY AND SIMPLE 
        VARIABLE OF SAME NAME.


THIS IS A TEST FOR A NON-STANDARD FEATURE OF MINIMAL BASIC.
TO PASS THIS TEST, THE PROCESSOR MUST EITHER:

   1) ACCEPT THE PROGRAM AND BE ACCOMPANIED BY DOCUMENTATION
      ACCURATELY DESCRIBING THE FEATURE'S INTERPRETATION
      BY THE PROCESSOR, OR

   2) REJECT THE PROGRAM WITH AN APPROPRIATE ERROR MESSAGE

SEE THE NBS MINIMAL BASIC TEST PROGRAMS USER'S MANUAL
FOR DETAILED CRITERIA.

               BEGIN TEST

VARIABLE A(I) WAS ASSIGNED 111*I + 5000,
AND SIMPLE VARIABLE A WAS ASSIGNED 777.
RESULTS BELOW:

A =  777 

A( 0 ) =  5000 
A( 1 ) =  5111 
A( 2 ) =  5222 
A( 3 ) =  5333 
A( 4 ) =  5444 
A( 5 ) =  5555 
A( 6 ) =  5666 
A( 7 ) =  5777 
A( 8 ) =  5888 
A( 9 ) =  5999 
A( 10 ) =  6110 

               END TEST

END PROGRAM 77
